-- HSBC Sells NZ$50 Million of 15-Year Discount Uridashi Notes
-- B y   H a r u m i   I c h i k u r a
-- 2012-01-11T14:01:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/hsbc-sells-nz-50-million-of-15-year-discount-uridashi-notes.html
The following uridashi bond went
on sale. Uridashi bonds are debt issued in the euromarket
and sold mainly to Japanese individual investors.  Issuer:            HSBC Bank plc
Amount:            NZ$50 million
Coupon:            0.50 percent of face value
Issue Price:       48.70 percent of face value
Duration:          15 years
Sales period:      Jan. 11 - Jan. 27
Settlement date:   Jan. 31, 2012
Maturity:          Jan. 29, 2027
Uridashi Manager:  Ando Securities Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Harumi Ichikura in London at   hichikura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  